{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"91bb89ab-e367-44a1-b2ab-98331f0b0704","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GPNwUGvvgyHU2fdZTgDmCi","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Configuring .NET crash dumps"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"46d49e2e-cc39-4b0a-9bf5-86865a243828","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me help them with:\n\n1. The environment variables needed to configure .NET crash dump collection\n2. The Kubernetes pod spec changes needed\n\nFor NativeAOT .NET apps, crash dump collection uses the `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` and related environment variables. Let me provide the configuration.\n\nKey environment variables for .NET crash dumps:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - Enable mini dump collection\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` controls the dump format (Normal, WithHeap, Triage, or Full)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` specifies where to save the dump files\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` enables additional diagnostics during dump creation\n- The newer `DOTNET_` prefix replaces the older `COMPlus_` convention\n\nFor NativeAOT in .NET 8 and later, crash dumps are handled through the `createdump` tool, which the user already has available.\n\nNow I need to outline the Kubernetes pod spec changes: setting up environment variables for dump configuration, adding a volume to persist the crash dumps, and pointing `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` to where the createdump tool is located.","outputTokens":460,"requestId":"1B82:2AB0E:15BA465:186D02F:6A0286E1"},"id":"20e5ab1a-410a-4de5-88e7-03f2e81bc022","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:48:29.500Z","parentId":"11debfe8-4e14-480d-a036-9378bec5dd41"}
