{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f0a6c5de-1b73-4edc-96d4-5e902ee1936b","content":"Here are the pod spec changes for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT on .NET 11:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: my-app\n    env:\n    # Enable automatic crash dump on unhandled exceptions / crashes\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n      value: \"1\"\n    # Dump type: 1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n      value: \"2\"\n    # Path to the createdump tool (required for NativeAOT)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n      value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n    # Dump file output path (%d = PID, %t = timestamp)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n      value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%d.%t\"\n    # Optional: enable createdump diagnostics logging\n    - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics\n      value: \"1\"\n    volumeMounts:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — required for NativeAOT since the runtime can't auto-locate `createdump`.\n- **`MiniDumpType=2`** (WithHeap) gives you managed heap data for debugging; use `4` (Full) if you need everything, but dumps will be much larger.\n- **`emptyDir`** works for ephemeral collection. Swap to a `persistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts, or add a sidecar to ship them to blob storage.\n- Set `sizeLimit` appropriately for your app's memory footprint — a full heap dump can match your container's memory limit.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"46d49e2e-cc39-4b0a-9bf5-86865a243828","outputTokens":498,"requestId":"1B82:2AB0E:15BCB24:186FC53:6A0286ED"},"id":"32f3ba36-a4ad-4f20-b5a5-b156456308ad","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:48:39.387Z","parentId":"5eed0efe-8bc0-4802-8d99-6dd0fa6426b1"}
